==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in [[w:1658|1658]], from Latin ''[[annulus]]'', from [[anus]] ''ring'', from [[PIE]] [[*ano-]] ''ring''. See also [[anal]], [[annular]], [[annelid]].

=== Noun ===
'''anus''' (''plural:'' [[anuses]])

# {{anatomy}} The lower opening of the digestive tract, through which [[feces]] pass.

